<font color="#FF0000">IT COMES AND GOES!!</font><br>
<tt>Sat Oct  4 22:39:49 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
It's another night of raging anger.  My wife is scared to death!  My mind goes numb before it comes and a shudder quakes my breath.  See the dead stacked up apile, the wind a balmy putrid.  Rain soaked bones are aching still. Life is all too lucid.  I recall not the pain of there or maybe now I do.  So am I ill nor will I will this agony on you?  There, Death!
<p><code>--   (Raymond Gerald  G Batt/65th Arty, 68-69 ) </code><p>


